            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> Belgis<supplied reason="lost">io<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="2"/>sacerdot<supplied reason="lost">i ad aram omnibus</supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>honorib</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">apud suos functo</supplied> <lb n="4"/>statuam <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">equestrem</supplied> <lb n="5"/>cum su<supplied reason="lost">bscriptione</supplied> <lb n="6"/>tres prov<supplied reason="lost">inciae Galliae</supplied> <lb n="7"/>primo u<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">mquam? ex? civit(ate)? sua</supplied> <lb n="8"/>ponend<supplied reason="lost">am curaverunt</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Gentiliz Belgisius ist Hapax. (B): CIL XIII: Z. 2: sacerdoti [ad aram ... omnibus]; Z. 3: honorib[us]. Rekonstruierte Gesamtbreite des Steins ca. 1,70 m.</p>
            </div>
